This paper deals with classification problems, which are typically studied in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus is on hierarchical classification, which involves a hierarchical relationship among the class labels, making it relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The approach is based on binary data, which is a common technique in data science and statistics (cs.DS).
